        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">You must Drag Two times.</para>
          <para styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Refer to the image to the left:</para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Interface2">FIRST DRAG</text>: from the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> to the <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> of the <text styleclass="Element">Arc</text>, then release you mouse.<text style="font-weight:bold;">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="Interface2">SECOND DRAG</text>: Position your pointer between the <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point </text>of the <text styleclass="Element">Arc</text>, and Drag towards the apex of the <text styleclass="Element">Arc</text> as you intend it to be drawn, then release your mouse.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">The <text styleclass="Element">Arc</text> has a <text styleclass="Interface">center-Point, </text>a <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point.</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">Circle</text><text style="font-style:italic;">n +</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text style="font-style:normal;">Point</text><text style="font-style:italic;">n</text><text style="font-style:normal;">&#32;</text><br/><text style="font-style:normal;">At each end of the </text><text styleclass="Element">Arc</text><text style="font-style:normal;">.</text></para>
        </td>
